i>, feminine of Old French <i>blanc</i> ‘white’ (of Germanic origin). It came to be associated with the notion of whiteness as indicating purity, and was introduced into England as a given name by the Normans. A pale complexion combined with light hair was long an ideal of beauty in Europe (compare Modern English <i>fair</i>, which at first meant ‘beautiful’ and then, from the 16th century, ‘light in colouring’)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Blanche de Pierepont-Sur-Avre was born in 1198, in Pierrepont-sur-Avre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France as the daughter of Robert de Pierrepont and Eustachie de Roucy. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with François 1er de Rosières en Santerre. She died in 1251, in Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1198–1251":"1198–1251","1189–1215":"1189–1215","1200–1251":"1200–1251","1184–1244":"1184–1244","1219–1281":"1219–1281","1223–1285":"1223–1285","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","–1221":"–1221","1198":"1198","1175":"1175","1285":"1285","1251":"1251","1184":"1184","1281":"1281","1215":"1215","1223":"1223","1244":"1244","ABT 1189":"umbes 1189","1200":"1200","1189":"1189","1221":"1221","1219":"1219","Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Pierrepont-sur-Avre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pierrepont-sur-Avre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Roucy, Aisne, France":"Roucy, Aisne, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1198–1251":"1198–1251","1189–1215":"1189–1215","1200–1251":"1200–1251","1184–1244":"1184–1244","1219–1281":"1219–1281","1223–1285":"1223–1285","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","–1221":"–1221","1198":"1198","1175":"1175","1285":"1285","1251":"1251","1184":"1184","1281":"1281","1215":"1215","1223":"1223","1244":"1244","ABT 1189":"noin 1189","1200":"1200","1189":"1189","1221":"1221","1219":"1219","Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Rosières-en-Santerre, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Pierrepont